To create an if/then statement in C, you use the if keyword followed by a condition enclosed in parentheses. If the condition is true, the code within the curly braces is executed. Here's an example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  printf("You are eligible to vote.");
}
```

In this example, if the age variable is equal to or greater than 18, the message "You are eligible to vote." will be printed.
